## 5. Implementation Roadmap

### Phase 1: MVP (Months 1-4)

**Goal:** Launch with core functionality for initial customers

**Features:**

- Tenant management & user authentication
- Basic supplier master data management
- Simple qualification workflow (3 stages)
- Manual evaluation (quarterly)
- Basic complaint tracking
- Simple dashboard (key metrics)
- REST API basics

**Success Metrics:**

- 5 pilot customers onboarded
- 50+ suppliers managed per customer
- System uptime > 99%

### Phase 2: Enhanced Features (Months 5-8)

**Goal:** Add differentiation & automation

**Features:**

- Advanced workflow engine (custom stages)
- Automated evaluation data collection
- Document management system
- Advanced CAPA tracking
- Custom fields & forms per tenant
- Email notifications & reminders
- First ERP integration (SAP or Salesforce)
- Advanced analytics & custom reports
- Mobile-responsive design

**Success Metrics:**

- 20 paying customers
- 2,000+ suppliers in platform
- 50% reduction in qualification time (vs. manual)

### Phase 3: Scale & Integrations (Months 9-12)

**Goal:** Become integration hub & scale

**Features:**

- Multiple ERP connectors (3-5 major ones)
- Webhook framework
- API marketplace/documentation portal
- Advanced dashboards & BI
- Supplier portal (self-service)
- Mobile app (iOS/Android)
- ML-powered risk prediction
- Benchmarking features
- White-label options

**Success Metrics:**

- 50+ customers
- 10,000+ suppliers
- 5+ active integrations
- NPS > 50

### Phase 4: Enterprise & AI (Months 13-18)

**Goal:** Enterprise features & intelligence

**Features:**

- AI-powered supplier recommendations
- Predictive performance scoring
- Automated root cause analysis
- Advanced security (SSO, SCIM)
- Compliance modules (ISO, automotive)
- Multi-language support
- Advanced workflow automation
- Blockchain for document verification (if relevant)

